Fatal Error: Unable to initialize UI5 CLI
Error [ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND]: Cannot find module '/home/user/projects/ysattravelinfo/node_modules/@ui5/cli/node_modules/@ui5/project/config/Configuration' imported from /home/user/projects/ysattravelinfo/node_mod

Solution:
That message means the UI5 CLI is starting, but it is loading a broken or mismatched install: Node is trying to load @ui5/project from inside @ui5/cli’s nested node_modules, and the file it expects (config/Configuration) is not there. That usually comes from a corrupt node_modules, a bad lockfile, or incompatible @ui5/cli / @ui5/project versions.
1. Clean reinstall (try this first)
In /home/user/projects/ysattravelinfo (your app root):
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm cache verify
npm install
npm run start

2. If it still fails: align UI5 tooling versions
Open package.json and check devDependencies for @ui5/cli, @sap/ux-ui5-tooling, and sometimes @ui5/middleware-*.
Prefer letting the Fiori generator / template versions stay as a set; avoid hand-picking very different major versions of @ui5/cli and @sap/ux-ui5-tooling.
Then:
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
npm run start

3. Optional: force a consistent @ui5/project
If the error still mentions @ui5/project, add an explicit compatible version (your team’s BAS might document the recommended pair; if not, match what a new Fiori Elements app from the wizard uses):
(or the version that matches your @ui5/cli major version), then reinstall as in step 1.
4. BAS / dev space
On SAP Business Application Studio, also try Terminal → new terminal after reinstall, and confirm you are in the folder that contains package.json for ysattravelinfo, not a parent monorepo folder.
Root cause in plain terms: the installed UI5 packages are incomplete or inconsistent, so @ui5/cli imports a path that does not exist in your tree. A full delete of node_modules + lockfile + npm install fixes this in most cases.
If you paste your package.json devDependencies (and the exact full error line if it continues after reinstall), we can suggest concrete version pins.
